{
  "abstract" : [
    {
      "text" : "Lindenmayer provides a library to develop and run your own Lindenmayer Systems.",
      "type" : "text"
    }
  ],
  "hierarchy" : {
    "paths" : [
      [

      ]
    ]
  },
  "identifier" : {
    "interfaceLanguage" : "swift",
    "url" : "doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer"
  },
  "kind" : "symbol",
  "metadata" : {
    "externalID" : "Lindenmayer",
    "modules" : [
      {
        "name" : "Lindenmayer"
      }
    ],
    "role" : "collection",
    "roleHeading" : "Library",
    "symbolKind" : "module",
    "title" : "Lindenmayer"
  },
  "primaryContentSections" : [
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "Overview",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Lindenmayer systems (also known as L-systems) are formalized rewriting tools used to create recursive fractals and organic shapes.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "The simplest form of an L-system uses a sequence of single characters, and a set of rules it applies to each element of the sequence, replacing it with one or more new elements.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "The sequence of elements are then interpreted, often using a turtle graphics metaphor, into a visual representation.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "This library implements a more advanced form L-system, known as a parametric, contextual L-system, inspired by book ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "http:\/\/algorithmicbotany.org\/papers\/abop\/abop.pdf",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "The library includes types and protocols to support building your own Lindenmayer systems and a number examples sourced from ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/L-system",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " and ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "http:\/\/algorithmicbotany.org\/papers\/",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " hosted at ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "http:\/\/algorithmicbotany.org\/",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "While the simplest forms of L-systems use single characters, this library defines the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/Module",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " protocol, which represents one of the elements.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "In addition to a number of built-in ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/Modules",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", you can define your own modules with properties that are made available to rewriting rules.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "To get support for using this package, see the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "https:\/\/github.com\/heckj\/Lindenmayer\/discussions",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " for questions and community feedback, or the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "https:\/\/github.com\/heckj\/Lindenmayer\/issues",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    }
  ],
